BRAND POSITIONING\par
Category: Direct-to-patient metabolic health + telehealth weight management.\par
Core promise: physician-led plans, clear pricing, and ongoing support so patients can sustain results.\par
Differentiators:\par
• Physician-led: real clinical oversight, not an anonymous intake funnel.\par
• Transparent: pricing, what’s included, and what happens if you’re not approved.\par
• Sustainable: coaching + monitoring to reduce churn and improve outcomes.\par
• Quality-first: pharmacy standards, cold-chain/shipping practices where applicable, and education.\par
AUDIENCE & USE CASES\par
• New prospects researching GLP-1 options and comparing providers.\par
• Patients who want a guided, accountable program (not just medication).\par
• People skeptical of compounding and looking for transparency and safety.\par
VOICE & TONE\par
Voice: calm, clinical, supportive. Avoid hype, shame, or aggressive urgency.\par
Tone rules:\par
• Lead with clarity and support (not fear or vanity).\par
• Use plain language; define clinical terms.\par
• Be transparent about risks and eligibility; don’t overpromise.\par
• Prefer evidence-forward phrasing: 'may', 'can help', 'results vary'.\par
MESSAGING FRAMEWORK\par
Primary headline formula:\par
• Outcome + credibility: 'Physician-led GLP-1 care that fits your life.'\par
• Speed + safety: 'Start online. Get reviewed by a licensed clinician.'\par
• Sustainability: 'A plan you can keep - not a quick fix.'\par
CTA language (preferred): Start Assessment • Check Eligibility • See Pricing • Talk to Support\par
