UI COMPONENTS (DESIGN DIRECTION)\par
• Buttons: rounded-12px, solid Teal on Navy/White; hover uses slightly darker Teal.\par
• Forms: large inputs, clear labels, inline validation, progress indicator for multi-step intake.\par
• Cards: soft border, slight shadow, lots of whitespace. Avoid clutter.\par
• Trust bar: clinician-reviewed, secure messaging, discreet shipping, support response times.\par
IMAGERY & ICONOGRAPHY\par
• Photography: real people, diverse ages/bodies, everyday life (not gym-only).\par
• Clinical visuals: use sparingly; favor warmth over 'sterile hospital' feel.\par
• Icons: thin/medium line icons; avoid cartoonish styles.\par
LOGO USAGE RULES\par
• Clear space: leave at least the height of the 'n' around the logo.\par
• Minimum size: mark >= 24px for UI; wordmark >= 120px wide for readability.\par
• Don’t stretch, skew, add shadows, or change colors outside the palette.\par
• Use the dark-background lockup on Navy backgrounds; use light lockup on white backgrounds.\par
